CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 16, 1957, pg. 3 reads: "This Is 2 Rooms - Mrs. Richard Faye prepares lunch on other side of a partial ceiling partition built in center of a large, old-fashioned, marble fireplace. The Fayes keep home neat, formerly lived at 1104 Wylie Ave., but had to move because of the Redevelopment."
TitMainTitle: Mrs. Richard Faye wearing dark skirt and light colored short sleeved blouse, seen through doorway standing in apartment kitchen, Western Avenue, North Side
